This paper discusses the design of a prototype called CSITE that uses Channel State Information (CSI) to authenticate Wi-Fi management frames. The paper focuses on wireless security and intrusion detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of off-the-shelf hardware and novel techniques to address challenges caused by user mobility and channel dynamics, which could fall under the categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), multimedia (cs.MM), and systems and control (cs.SY).
